{
  "texts": [
    "These papers have produced a number of approaches to this problem.",
    "However, the approach taken by these papers does not map directly into our ndings.",
    "We do not have a standard panel dataset, with each treated unit (a judge) having a single observation in each time period (a year).",
    "Our data is at the case level, and judges could have multiple cases, one case, or no cases (in a given outcome class) in a given year.",
    "We must include circuit-year xed eects to obtain block randomization of judges to cases, so we cannot aggregate up to the judge-year level."
  ]
}